Definition: an atom or group of atoms with at least one unpaired electron
Example: in the body it is usually an oxygen molecule that has lost an electron and will stabilize itself by stealing an electron from a nearby molecule; in the body free radicals are high-energy particles that ricochet wildly and damage cells
Synonyms: radical, atom, an, or, group, of, atoms, with, at, least, one, unpaired, electron, in, the, body, it, is, usually, oxygen, molecule, that, has, lost, and, will, stabilize, itself, by, stealing, from, a, nearby, free, radicals, are, high-energy, particles, ricochet, wildly, damage, cells
Category: noun.substance
